reviewText:
Pros:  Engaging and challenging campaign;
Almost endless replayability via user generated content or multiplayer;
Relatively easy to get in to;
Diverse multiplayer community;
New user generated content (maps, guns, vehicles, overhaul mods, missions, etc.);
All in one game (FPS, RPG, RTS, etc. modes available);
Pleasing to the eye;
Gives you the possibility to brag about knowing how to clear buildings, stay in formation and etc.;
Training given by military personell who play this game can help you in real life (incl. paintball and airsoft);Cons:  Can be buggy at times (especially when new patches come out);
Spotty AI performance (from full derp to terminator);
Semi-steep learning curve for basic gameplay (attachments, maps, weapon sway etc.);
Very steep learning curve for expert gameplay (formations, chain of command, team synergy, etc.);
Taxing on your gaming rig (lack of good hardware can limit your tactical possibilities in-game);
People will probably hate you at how good at firefights you will become (in games and real life); In general:
Your creativity and acting is the only limit in this game. With an active modding community, zeus gameplay, RP-oriented clans, PvP servers, survival, orientation and other scenarios, this single game can cover quite a few of your demands for digital entertainment. Irrelevant if you are a hardcore military fan or a casual player, you can find something that tickles your fancy.

You can fight war without clothes on;
Explosions everywhere;
Destroy pretty much any vehicle with fences;
Desync. galore!

What's not to love about this game!
